<subSubSection id="C3276553F00AFFB4FF0DF9DBFB9BF84E" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F00AFFB4FF0DF9DBFC2DF8DE" blockId="9.[151,1437,1449,2015]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FF0DF9DBFEEDF9E6" bold="true" box="[199,315,1629,1655]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is one of the largest of the genus (BL up to 40.0 mm) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B29F00AFFB4FB83F9DBFA8AF9E9" author="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[1097,1372,1629,1656]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" refId="ref11172" refString="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of living chitons. 1. Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina. E. J. Brill / W., Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle 1985</bibRefCitation>
). The studied specimen is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="5486887AF00AFFB4FDD2F907FD54F90A" box="[536,642,1665,1691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">lectotype</typeStatus>
, which I have examined. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B29F00AFFB4FC69F907FB16F90D" author="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[931,1216,1665,1692]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" refId="ref11172" refString="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of living chitons. 1. Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina. E. J. Brill / W., Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle (1985)</bibRefCitation>
gave a detailed description of the 
<typeStatus id="5486887AF00AFFB4FE8DF923FE78F92E" box="[327,430,1701,1727]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">lectotype</typeStatus>
with drawings of the valves, armature of girdle and radula. However, there is a mistake in the description of the radula. The head of the major lateral tooth of the radula of the 
<typeStatus id="5486887AF00AFFB4FB80F94FFB67F972" box="[1098,1201,1737,1763]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">lectotype</typeStatus>
is not unidentate but bidentate. The Philippine specimen possesses 13 gills on each side arranged from valve VI to near the anus, and a radula that is 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF00AFFB4FEE7F897FE55F8BA" box="[301,387,1809,1835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
long with 53 transverse rows of mature teeth. Each granule of the tegmentum in the examined specimen has seven to nine pores of aesthetes. The 
<typeStatus id="5486887AF00AFFB4FD1CF8B3FCEBF8DE" box="[726,829,1845,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">lectotype</typeStatus>
has seven pores.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F00AFFB4FF0DF8DFFB9BF84E" blockId="9.[151,1437,1449,2015]" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF00AFFB4FDE0F8DCFD0CF8E2" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[554,730,1882,1907]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FDE0F8DCFD0CF8E2" box="[554,730,1882,1907]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having granules in the central areas with seven to nine aesthete pores (vs. 18 to 21 pores in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF00AFFB4FD53F8F8FC9CF806" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[665,842,1918,1943]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FD53F8F8FC9CF806" box="[665,842,1918,1943]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and subcarinated valves (vs. usually rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF00AFFB4FA4CF8F8FEFEF82A" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FA4CF8F8FEFEF82A" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Moreover in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF00AFFB4FE05F824FDFCF82A" baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[463,554,1954,1979]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rissoi">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FE05F824FDFCF82A" box="[463,554,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">L. rissoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the granules on the longitudinal rows of the central areas are located at a small distance to each other; however they are very close to each other in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF00AFFB4FC45F840FBEBF84E" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[911,1085,1990,2015]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="476" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF00AFFB4FC45F840FBEBF84E" box="[911,1085,1990,2015]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="476">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
